Class AbstractStructureParser

java.lang.Object
gov.cdc.izgw.v2tofhir.segment.AbstractStructureParser
All Implemented Interfaces:
StructureParser
Direct Known Subclasses:
AbstractSegmentParser
public abstract class AbstractStructureParser extends Object implements StructureParser
This is an abstract implementation for StructureParser instances used by the MessageParser.

    • findResource

      public <R extends org.hl7.fhir.r4.model.Resource> R findResource(Class<R> clazz, String id)
      Find a resource of the specified type for this parsing session, or create one if none can be found or id is null or empty. This method is typically called by the first segment of a group that is associated with a given resource. It can be used to create a resource with a given id value if control is needed over the id value.
      Type Parameters:
      R - The type of resource
      Parameters:
      clazz - The sepecified type for the resource to create
      id - The identifier to assign.
      Returns:
      A new resource of the specified type. The id will already be populated.

    • parse

      public void parse(ca.uhn.hl7v2.model.Segment segment)
      Annotation driven parsing. Call this method to use parsing driven by ComesFrom and Produces annotations in the parser. This method will be called by MessageParser for each segment of the given type that appears within the method. It will create the primary resource produced by the parser (by calling the setup() method) and then parses individual fields of the segment and passes them to parser methods to add them to the primary resource or to create any extra resources.
      Parameters:
      segment - The segment to be parsed

    • setup

      public abstract org.hl7.fhir.instance.model.api.IBaseResource setup()
      Set up any resources that field handlers will use. Used during initialization of field handlers as well as during a normal parse operation. NOTE: Setup can look at previously parsed items to determine if there is any work to do in the context of the current message.
      Returns:
      the primary resource being created by this parser, or null if parsing in this context should do nothing.
